<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Block-level replaced elements with auto margins</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#inline-replaced-height" />
        <meta name="flags" content="image" />
        <meta name="assert" content="Verify block level replaced elements in normal flow with margin-top or margin-bottom set to auto result in a used value of '0'." />
        <style type="text/css">
            div
            {
                border: 3px solid green;
            }
            img
            {
                display: block;
                margin-top: auto;
                margin-bottom: auto;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if no white space is in between the top and bottom edges of the blue box and the green borders.</p>
        <div>
            <img src="../../../Support/blue100x33.png" alt="Test Image" />
        </div>
    </body>
</html>